President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key roles in his administration. Christopher R. Hill is nominated for Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Serbia. He is a career member of the foreign service and has held various positions, including U.S. Ambassador to Iraq, Korea, Poland, and Macedonia. Ravi Chaudhary is nominated for Assistant Secretary of the Air Force for Installations, Energy, and the Environment. He previously served as a Senior Executive at the U.S. Department of Transportation and is a former Air Force officer and pilot. Ann Phillips is nominated for Administrator of the United States Maritime Administration at the Department of Transportation. She is currently the Special Assistant to the Governor of Virginia for Coastal Adaptation and Protection and served for 31 years in the United States Navy. Glen S. Fukushima is nominated for Member of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation. He is a Senior Fellow at the Center for American Progress and has extensive experience in U.S. relations with Asia. Enoh T. Ebong is nominated for Director of the United States Trade and Development Agency. She previously served in various roles at the agency and most recently as its Acting Director. These nominations are subject to confirmation by the Senate.